<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1532" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1532">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/57.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">French Chargé &amp;
                                        Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Manchester</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I beg to thank your excellency for what the Department of State has
                                already done in regard to French citizens imprisoned at Zacatecas.
                                Pending the moment when the President and yourself will be able to
                                receive me I should be greatly obliged to your excellency if he
                                would prescribe an immediate inquest tending to ascertain the
                                correctness of the information that reached our Legation in Mexico
                                City concerning the murder of two French Christian Brothers, Messrs.
                                Astru and Gilles, shot at Zacatecas on Villa’s order and if he would
                                keep me informed of the result of that inquest.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Clausse</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>